WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.800 --> 00:00:06.869
Checking an entry means understanding whether the available evidence supports it.

2
00:00:06.869 --> 00:00:16.021
Vera starts from the sampled journal row and searches the documents provided and any authorized archives or exports.

3
00:00:16.021 --> 00:00:23.411
It compares amount, date, document number, description and counterparty while keeping every source visible.

4
00:00:23.411 --> 00:00:34.765
Strong matches move into the supported set. Ambiguous cases remain in the review queue with the reason and the specific document to inspect.

5
00:00:34.765 --> 00:00:44.797
The result is a workpaper that links every checked entry to its evidence, separates exceptions and preserves the verification path.

6
00:00:44.797 --> 00:00:49.200
From a sampled row to support the reviewer can follow.
